Automation Tool ---> Rest assured 

Task1: Getting all the repo from the user's account. 

@Test(enabled = True, description = "Getting all Repository")
	public void gettingAllRepository() {

		given()
			.auth()  
			.oauth2("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")   
		.when()
			.get("https://api.github.com/user/repos")
		.then()
			.log()
			.body()
			.statusCode(200);}
      
  Terms :
  .auth()  ----> to specify there is authentication 
  .oauth2("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")  ------> to specify which authentication and it has that API key generated by the user
  .get("https://api.github.com/user/repos") --------> get all the user repos !
  .statusCode ---- is a code which is used when a client requests something from the user .
  
  
  Part2: Create Repo 
  @Test(enabled=false, description = "For creating a repo")
		  public void createRepo() {
			  
			  JSONObject param = new JSONObject();        //Its a json object , 
			  
			  param.put("name", "RestAssuredRepo");                    //to name the repo!
			  param.put("description", "Created on August 3rd");              //to have the desc of the repo!
			  param.put("homepage", "https://github.com/ahad1105");         //for the homepage of the user's account
			   
			   given()
			  		.header("Content-Type", "application/json")
			  		.body(param.toJSONString())
			  		.auth()
					.oauth2("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")
			  .when()
				  .post("https://api.github.com/user/repos")
			  .then()
				  .log()
				  .body()
				  .statusCode(201);   
	}
  
  
  part3: delete a repo
  
  @Test(enabled = true, description = "Deleting repo")
			public void DeleteRepository() {

				given()
					.auth()  //to specify there is authentication
				
					.oauth2("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")//to specify which authentication
				.when()
					.delete("https://api.github.com/repos/ahad1105/RestAssuredRepo")    //give url of the repo
				
				.then()
					.log()
					.body()
					.statusCode(404);}
  
